NodeDefinition.Name: BasicNode
NodeDefinition.Author: Simio Employee
NodeDefinition.Description: A BasicNode object may be used by an entity to transfer into or out of an object. This type of node may also be used to define an intersection point in a network of links.

ChangeDescriptions.ChangeDescription: Version 2.36: Renamed the 'TransferToLinkFailureLogic' process in the BasicNode process logic to 'TransferFailureLogic'. If the 'AutoTransferOnEntry' property value of the BasicNode is 'To Parent External Node' and the transfer to the specified parent external node fails, then the token now executes the 'TransferFailureLogic' process.
Version 2.37: Changed 'Capacity' display name to 'Initial Capacity' as object capacities are now user assignable.
Version 2.39: Updated the BasicNode object process logic to specify all of the object's process delays as non-interruptible.
Version 2.40: In the object process logic, the 'Action' property for all Execute steps executing an 'add-on process' is now specified as 'WaitUntilCompleted'.
Version 2.41: Minor property description and display name updates.
Version 3.42: Changes related to setting the 'Token Associated Object Destroyed Action' option for process logic in this object.
Version 3.44: 'SeizedObjects.UnitsOwned' function renamed to 'SeizedObjects.CapacityUnitsOwned'.
Version 3.47: Added new 'Appearance' property category.
Version 3.48: Hide new 'Random Number Stream' property in 'Routing Logic' category.
Version 3.49: Specified the 'OnAssociatedObjectTransferRequested' property of some processes as 'EndProcess'.

Version 3.54: Added new Notify step to 'TransferFailureLogic' process to output a warning if automatically destroying an entity. Conversion to 'OnRunInitialized' standard interface process. Added 'Run Ending' add-on process trigger.
Version 3.56: Added new 'Tally Statistics' property category.
Version 3.57: Change to new 'OnEnteredParking' standard interface process that was added to Simio's base node object.

Version 4.58: Removed 'AutoTransferOnEntry' property. The 'ExternalNodeName' property is now always visible with display name 'Bound External Output Node'. If a transfer to parent external node attempt fails, then the token now continues normal processing instead of executing the 'TransferFailureLogic'. Added new 'Advanced Options' property category.
Version 4.60: Process logic now uses new object 'SeizedResources.CapacityUnitsOwned' function instead of deprecated 'SeizedObjects.CapacityUnitsOwned'.
Version 4.61: Set all inherited properties in 'Financials' category to not be visible.
Version 4.63: Set all inherited properties in 'Financials->Resource Costs' to not be visible.
Version 4.65: Process logic now uses new object 'SeizedResources.CapacityOwnedOf' function instead of deprecated 'SeizedResources.CapacityUnitsOwned'.

Version 4.66: If bound to an external output node of the parent model, a basic node's 'Entered' event is still fired and its 'Entered' add-on process trigger still executed before transferring the entity out of the parent model.

Version 4.68: The BasicNode object is no longer enabled as a resource object, and the 'InitialCapacity', 'RankingRule', and 'RankingExpression' properties have been replaced by equivalent 'InitialTravelerCapacity', 'EntryRankingRule', and 'EntryRankingExpression' properties. Renamed 'InitializedAddOnProcess' property to 'RunInitializedAddOnProcess'. Renamed 'ExternalNodeName' property to 'BoundExternalOutputNode'.
Version 4.73: New 'Random Number Stream' property now available in the 'Advanced Options' category.

Version 4.74: If a traveler is attempting to transfer out of the node and has no network assigned (i.e., is using free space for travel), then the node's process logic now transfers the traveler into free space.
Version 4.77: Removed an unnecessary 'TransferFailureLogic' Execute step from the 'OnEnteredToAssociatedObject' process logic.
Version 5.87: Process logic now uses new property 'HasValue' function instead of deprecated 'IsDefined'.
Version 5.91: Added information to indicate which properties to display if the new 'Show Commonly Used Properties Only' option is enabled.
Version 6.103: Some property description updates.
Version 7.130: Renamed 'RandomNumberStream' property to 'BranchingRandomNumberStream'
Version 7.131: Added new 'Routing Logic -> Other Routing Out Options' property category with possible 'Branching Random Number Stream' property.
Version 8.133 'OnEntered' process logic no longer requires a Decide 'IfFreeSpaceTraveler' step. Added 'State Assignments' property category.
Version 8.134 'Routing Logic -> Other Routing Out Options -> Random Number Stream' property now inherited from the base node definition
Version 8.137 'TransferFailureLogic' now gives warning notification if automatically parking entity.
Version 8.147: Property description string updates.
Version 12.212: Renamed 'TalliesOnEnteringValue' property to 'TalliesOnEnteringValueExpression'. Renamed 'TalliesOnExitedValue' property to 'TalliesOnExitedValueExpression'.

LinkDefinition.Name: Path
LinkDefinition.Author: Simio Employee
LinkDefinition.Description: A Path object may be used to define a pathway between two node locations where the travel time is determined by the path length and a traveling entity's speed. Passing may or may not be allowed.

ChangeDescriptions.ChangeDescription: Version 2.39: Updated the Path object to provide a 'State Assignments' property category.

Version 2.40: Removed the Path object's 'Close' and 'Open' public processes. For equivalent functionality, use the Assign step and assign the path's DesiredDirection state to the value 'Enum.TrafficDirection.None' to close entry onto the path, or to the value 'Enum.TrafficDirection.Either' to re-open entry onto the path. In the object process logic, the 'Action' property for all Execute steps executing an 'add-on process' is now specified as 'WaitUntilCompleted'.
Version 2.41: Updated the assignments repeat groups to take state units into account.
Version 3.42: Changes related to setting the 'Token Associated Object Destroyed Action' option for process logic in this object.
Version 3.47: Added new 'Appearance' property category.
Version 3.49: Specified the 'OnAssociatedObjectTransferRequested' property of some processes as 'EndProcess'.
Version 3.51: Do not display new link 'Cell Spacing Type', 'Cell Size', and 'Auto Align Cells' properties.
Version 3.54: Conversion to 'OnRunInitialized' standard interface process. Added 'Run Ending' add-on process trigger.
Version 3.57: Added logic for new 'OnTurnedAround' standard interface process.
Version 4.58: Added new 'Advanced Options' property category.
Version 4.59: Process logic now uses new entity 'NextEntityAheadOnLink' function instead of deprecated 'FrontTraffic.Speed' function
Version 4.61: Set all inherited properties in 'Financials' category to not be visible.
Version 4.63: Reordered the position of the 'Financials' property category.
Version 4.68: Changed 'TravelerCapacity' integer property to 'InitialTravelerCapacity' expression property. Renamed 'InitializedAddOnProcess' property to 'RunInitializedAddOnProcess'.
Version 4.76: Updates required due to Suspend & Resume step enhancements.
Version 5.85: Process logic changes to better support an entity on the path being destroyed before reaching the end of the link.
Version 5.87: Process logic now uses new property 'HasValue' function instead of deprecated 'IsDefined'.
Version 5.88: 'OnCollisionCleared' process - Improvements to entity movement rate assignment expression to better avoid null pointer exceptions.
Version 5.91: Added information to indicate which properties to display if the new 'Show Commonly Used Properties Only' option is enabled.
Version 6.103: Some property description updates.
Version 8.147: Property description string updates.
Version 9.161: New TokenMatchCondition property added to Suspend & Resume steps.
Version 9.164: OnCollisionCleared process logic - Fixed entity movement rate assignment expression to never assign a value greater than the entity's desired speed.

FixedDefinition.Name: Server
FixedDefinition.Author: Simio Employee
FixedDefinition.Description: A Server object may be used to model a capacity-constrained processing location. Operations performed at the server can be modeled as either a processing time or as a sequence of tasks. Secondary resources or material requirements may be optionally specified.

ChangeDescriptions.ChangeDescription: Version 2.37: Changed 'Capacity' display name to 'Initial Capacity' as object capacities are now user assignable.

Version 2.39: Updated the Server object process logic to specify all of the object's process delays as non-interruptible except for the 'TransferInTime' and 'ProcessingTime' delays in the 'OnEnteredProcessing' process. The 'OnEnteredProcessing' process was changed from a private process to a public process. Added a 'State Assignments' property category.

Version 2.40: 'On Shift' or 'Off Shift' add-on process triggers are now called when initializing the object even if a work schedule is not specified. In the object process logic, the 'Action' property for all Execute steps executing an 'add-on process' is now specified as 'WaitUntilCompleted'. Restructured the failure-related process logic.
Version 2.41: Updated the assignments repeat groups to take state units into account.

Version 3.42: Changes related to setting the 'Token Associated Object Destroyed Action' option for process logic in this object. The EntryRankingRule and EntryRankingExpression properties of the InputBuffer station were changed to be the same as the Server's resource ranking rule.
Version 3.44: 'SeizedObjects.UnitsOwned' function renamed to 'SeizedObjects.CapacityUnitsOwned'.
Version 3.47: Added a 'Secondary Resources' property category. Added new 'Appearance' property category.

Version 3.49: Specified the 'OnAssociatedObjectTransferRequested' property of some processes as 'EndProcess'. Collapsed the 'Secondary Resources->Other Resource Seizes' & 'Secondary Resources->Other Resource Releases' property categories by default.
Version 3.50: Updated the description text for some of the secondary resource related properties.
Version 3.52: If the model's 'Disable Randomness' option is being used, the object's 'Reliability Logic' is now automatically disabled to not generate any failure occurrences.
Version 3.53: Property display names 'Request Visit', 'Node Name', and 'Visit Priority' renamed to 'Request Move', 'Destination Node', and 'Move Priority'.

Version 3.54: Usage of 'Run.RandomnessDisabled' function instead of deprecated 'DisableRandomness' function. Added support for 'Processing Time Based' failure type. Conversion to 'OnRunInitialized' standard interface process. Added 'Run Ending' add-on process trigger.
Version 3.56: Conversion to 'OnEvaluatingSeizeRequest' standard interface process.
Version 4.58: Added new 'Advanced Options' property category.
Version 4.60: Process logic now uses new object 'SeizedResources.CapacityUnitsOwned' function instead of deprecated 'SeizedObjects.CapacityUnitsOwned'.
Version 4.61: Added new 'Financials' property category.
Version 4.62: Added new 'Financials->Buffer Costs property category.

Version 4.63: Reordered the position of the 'Financials' property category. 'Processing' add-on process trigger now always executed after entity enters the 'Processing' station. Added new 'Financials->Resource Costs' property category.
Version 4.64: Added a 'Random' selection goal option to the 'Secondary Resources' functionality.

Version 4.65: Process logic now uses new object 'SeizedResources.CapacityOwnedOf' function instead of deprecated 'SeizedResources.CapacityUnitsOwned'. 'Repairing' add-on process trigger marked as obsolete and is no longer displayed in the Properties window if not previously defined.

Version 4.68: Simplified 'OnExitedProcessing' process by eliminating Decide step to check whether token has an associated object. Renamed 'InitializedAddOnProcess' property to 'RunInitializedAddOnProcess'. Added new 'Before Processing' add-on process trigger.

Category.Name: Table Row Referencing/Before Processing
Category.Description: Table Row Reference Actions Before Processing

ExpressionProperty.Name: TransferInTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: The time required to transfer an entity into this object.

EnumProperty.Name: ProcessType
EnumProperty.Description: The method used to model the processing of an entity.

ExpressionProperty.Name: ProcessingTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: The time required to process an entity.

RepeatingProperty.Name: ProcessingTasks
RepeatingProperty.Description: The set of tasks required to process an entity.

IntegerProperty.Name: TaskIDNumber
IntegerProperty.Description: Integer number used to identify the task in the Immediate Predecessors or Immediate Successors field of another task.

SequenceNumberProperty.Name: TaskSequenceNumber
SequenceNumberProperty.Description:
Sequence number used to define the task precedence constraints. To model a task sequence that is simply a serially ordered set of tasks, define the tasks with increasing sequence numbers (e.g., the first task is numbered '10', the second task is numbered '20', and so forth). Tasks with identical sequence numbers will be performed in parallel.
For a more in-depth discussion on task sequence numbering including examples of how to model parallel subsequences, please refer to the Task Sequence element documentation.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskBranchType
EnumProperty.Description:
Indicates whether the task is always performed, or whether it is instead treated as the first task of a conditional or probabilistic branch in the process workflow.
If the branch type is Conditional, then the task is performed if the specified logical condition evaluates to True. Otherwise, the task is cancelled.
The Probabilistic branch type may be used to identify the task as one of possibly several mutually exclusive alternatives at a probabilistic decision point. The sum of the branch probabilities at a probabilistic decision point cannot be greater than one.
If the branch type is Independent Probabilistic, then the tasks specified probability is independent of and thus not affected by other probabilistic branching. For example, if a decision point has two task branches each with an independent probability of 0.5 (50% chance), then that indicates either, both, or neither of the branches might be required to occur. And the probability of both branches being required is (0.5)*(0.5) = 0.25 (25% chance).

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description: The branch condition or probability specified as an expression. If a condition then enter the logical condition. If a probability then enter the chance of performing the task as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).

EnumProperty.Name: TaskProcessType
EnumProperty.Description: The method used to model the processing of the task.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskProcessingTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: The time required to perform the task.

ElementProperty.Name: TaskProcessName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the process that will be executed in order to perform the task. The task will be considered finished once this invoked process has ended.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskSubmodelEntityCreationMethod
EnumProperty.Description:
The method used to create an entity that will be sent to some other distinct part of the overall model. The task will be considered finished once this created submodel entity has ended its processing (i.e., been destroyed).
If copying the original entity's attributes, then all possible state values and table references will be copied from the original entity to the created submodel entity.

DynamicObjectInstanceProperty.Name: TaskSubmodelEntityType
DynamicObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The entity type of the created submodel entity.

NodeProperty.Name: TaskSubmodelStartingNode
NodeProperty.Description: The facility node location that the created submodel entity will be sent to in order to start its processing.

StateProperty.Name: TaskSaveOriginalEntityReference
StateProperty.Description: Optional entity reference state variable to save a reference to the original entity being processed at the server. Typically is a state variable defined on the created submodel entity, to allow easy access by that entity to the original entity's attributes.

ElementProperty.Name: TaskChangeoverLogicName
ElementProperty.Description:
The name of the Changeover Logic element used to determine any sequence dependent setup times.
Go to Definitions->Elements to add a new Changeover Logic element to the model.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskResourceEfficiencyRule
EnumProperty.Description:
The processing rule used to alter the rate at which the task is performed if there are seized resources with defined efficiency values. The actual task duration is the planned task duration divided by the efficiency.
If the rule is None, then seized resource efficiency is ignored.
If the rule is Average, then the average seized resource efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Count, then the number of seized resources with a defined efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Maximum, then the largest efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Minimum, then the smallest efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Sum, then the sum of the seized resource efficiency values is used.

TaskDependencyProperty.Name: TaskImmediatePredecessors
TaskDependencyProperty.Description: Lists the ID numbers of the tasks which must be finished or cancelled before this task can start. To specify more than one predecessor, enter multiple task ID numbers separated by commas.

TaskDependencyProperty.Name: TaskImmediateSuccessors
TaskDependencyProperty.Description: Lists the ID numbers of the tasks which can't start until this task is finished or cancelled. To specify more than one successor, enter multiple task ID numbers separated by commas.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskAutoCancelTrigger
EnumProperty.Description:
Event type that will trigger an automatic cancellation of the task.
The default setting is 'All Immediate Predecessors Cancelled', which indicates the task will be automatically cancelled if all its immediate predecessors in the task sequence are cancelled. This default setting is recommended if you want conditional or probabilistic branching to automatically cancel all tasks in unselected branches.
For a more in-depth discussion of this option including examples, please refer to the Task Sequence element documentation.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsResourceType
EnumProperty.Description: The method for specifying the resource object(s) to seize.

ObjectInstanceProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsResourceName
ObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The name of the resource object to seize.

ListNameProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsResourceListName
ListNameProperty.Description: The name of the object list from which to select the resource object(s) to seize.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsSelectionGoal
EnumProperty.Description: The rule used to select a resource object from multiple candidates.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsSelectionValueExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The expression used to get the value for each candidate resource.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource objects (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

EnumProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsRequestMove
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates whether a move to a specified node will be requested from the seized resource(s). The task will not be able to start until arrival of the resource(s) at the node location.

NodeProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsDestinationNode
NodeProperty.Description: The name of the destination node that the seized resource(s) will be requested to move to.

ListProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsOffShiftRule
ListProperty.Description:
The processing rule used if a resource is at the end of a shift because of its specified work schedule.
Suspend Processing - The processing of the task will be immediately suspended. Processing will resume at the start of the resources next shift.
Finish Work Already Started - The processing of the task will be allowed to continue until finished. The resource will not be allowed to accept any new work.
Switch Resources If Possible - The processing of the task will be immediately suspended. The affected entity will then try to resume the tasks processing as soon as possible by releasing the resource and seizing another available one that satisfies the same task resource requirements.
NOTE: This property setting may vary from task to task but not from resource requirement to resource requirement for the same task. Thus, if using a table driven approach to define task sequence data, the value of this property may only be specified as a constant or by referencing a column in the table that defines each individual processing task.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsNumberOfResources
ExpressionProperty.Description: The number of individual resource objects to seize capacity units of.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsUnitsPerResource
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The number of capacity units to seize per candidate resource.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource objects (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsSelectionCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional condition evaluated for each candidate resource that must be true for the resource to be selected.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource objects (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsResourceEfficiency
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional value that can alter the rate at which the task is performed using the seized resource(s), expressed as a fraction. The actual task duration is the planned task duration divided by the efficiency. Hence, an efficiency value greater than 1 shortens the time and a value less than 1 lengthens the time.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource objects (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).
Set this property to blank to declare the resource efficiency as undefined.

BooleanProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsMustSimultaneouslySeize
BooleanProperty.Description:
If multiple resources are required for the task, indicates whether all of the resources must be available before any can be seized.
NOTE: This property setting may vary from task to task but not from resource requirement to resource requirement for the same task. Thus, if using a table driven approach to define task sequence data, the value of this property may only be specified as a constant or by referencing a column in the table that defines each individual processing task.

BooleanProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsImmediatelyTrySeize
BooleanProperty.Description:
Indicates whether to immediately try seizing the task resource requirements before the execution of any other simulation logic in the system and, if successful, skipping the resource allocation queues.
Setting this property to False will just insert the seize request into the resource allocation queues. An evaluation of those queues will then be scheduled on the simulations current event calendar as a late priority event.
NOTE: This property setting may vary from task to task but not from resource requirement to resource requirement for the same task. Thus, if using a table driven approach to define task sequence data, the value of this property may only be specified as a constant or by referencing a column in the table that defines each individual processing task.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsKeepReservedCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Once the task has completed and released the resource requirements, an optional condition indicating whether to keep the released resource capacity reserved for possible later reuse by the same entity. Other entities will be unable to use a reserved resource unless the reservation is cancelled.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the task resource object(s) being released (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).
Note that when an entity is attempting to select a resource from a group of candidates (e.g., from a list or from a population of some resource type), by default a preference will be given to select a resource that has already been reserved by that entity irrespective of the specified selection goal.
Leaving this property blank (no condition) is equivalent to entering False.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsReservationTimeout
ExpressionProperty.Description:
If the keep reserved condition is true, then an optional wait time before automatically cancelling the reservation.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the task resource object(s) being released (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

BooleanProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsImmediatelyTryAllocateWhenReleased
BooleanProperty.Description:
Once the task has completed and released the resource requirements, indicates whether to immediately try allocating the released resource capacity to waiting seize requests before the execution of any other simulation logic in the system.
Setting this property to False will skip immediate allocation. Instead, an evaluation of the resource allocation queues will be scheduled on the simulations current event calendar as a late priority event.
NOTE: This property setting may vary from task to task but not from resource requirement to resource requirement for the same task. Thus, if using a table driven approach to define task sequence data, the value of this property may only be specified as a constant or by referencing a column in the table that defines each individual processing task.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskResourceRequirementsSkipRequirementCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: Optional condition indicating whether to skip the resource requirement. Is evaluated only once per task, at the start of execution of the underlying Seize step.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsActionType
EnumProperty.Description: The type of material-related action required.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsConsumptionType
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates whether to consume a single material or a bill of materials. The material consumption will be required to start the processing of the task.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsProductionType
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates whether to produce a single material or a bill of materials. The material production will occur after finishing the processing of the task.

ElementProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsMaterialName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the material which is to be either specifically consumed or produced, or whose bill of materials is to be consumed or produced.

EnumProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsInventorySiteType
EnumProperty.Description:
Indicates the fixed object that is the inventory location. Applies only to material elements whose Location Based Inventory property is set to True.
The 'ParentObject' setting may be used to indicate that the inventory site is the server, combiner, or separator.

ObjectInstanceProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsSiteObjectName
ObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The name of the fixed object that is the inventory location.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsQuantity
ExpressionProperty.Description: The quantity to be consumed or produced.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsLotID
ExpressionProperty.Description: Optional string value indicating the lot identifier of the consumed or produced material.

BooleanProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsMustSimultaneouslyConsume
BooleanProperty.Description:
Indicates whether all of the task's required materials must be available before any can be consumed.
NOTE: This property setting may vary from task to task but not from material requirement to material requirement for the same task. Thus, if using a table driven approach to define task sequence data, the value of this property may only be specified as a constant or by referencing a column in the table that defines each individual processing task.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsProductionDelayTime
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional delay time after task is finished before producing the material and adding it to inventory.
NOTE: This property has been deprecated. Use a Delay step or additional task instead. To edit a deprecated property, go to File->Settings->GUI->Display Deprecated Properties In Properties Window and change that setting to True.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskMaterialRequirementsSkipRequirementCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: Optional condition indicating whether to skip the material requirement. Is evaluated only once per task, at the start of execution of the underlying Consume or Produce step.

ListProperty.Name: TaskStateAssignmentsTrigger
ListProperty.Description:
Indicates when to perform the state assignment.
Task Ready is when all of the tasks predecessor dependencies have been satisfied and the entity is about to try seizing or consuming the resources and materials needed (if any) to perform the task.
Starting Task is when all of the task's resource and material requirements (if any) have been satisfied and the processing of the task is about to begin.
Finished Task is when the processing of the task has been finished.

StateProperty.Name: TaskStateAssignmentsStateVariableName
StateProperty.Description: Name of the state variable that will be assigned a new value.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskStateAssignmentsNewValue
ExpressionProperty.Description: The new value to assign.

ElementProperty.Name: TaskReadyAddOnProcess
ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when all of the tasks predecessor dependencies have been satisfied and the entity is about to try seizing or consuming the resources and materials needed (if any) to perform the task.

ElementProperty.Name: StartingTaskAddOnProcess
ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when all of the task's resource and material requirements (if any) have been satisfied and the processing of the task is about to begin.

ElementProperty.Name: FinishedTaskAddOnProcess
ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when the processing of the task has been finished.

RepeatingProperty.Name: ProcessingLoopbackBranches
RepeatingProperty.Description: Conditional or probabilistic loopback branches in the task workflow.

IntegerProperty.Name: LoopbackFromTaskIDNumber
IntegerProperty.Description: The task ID number that is the beginning of the loopback.

IntegerProperty.Name: LoopbackToTaskIDNumber
IntegerProperty.Description: The task ID number that is the end of the loopback.

SequenceNumberProperty.Name: LoopbackFromTaskSequenceNumber
SequenceNumberProperty.Description: The task sequence number that is the beginning of the loopback.

SequenceNumberProperty.Name: LoopbackToTaskSequenceNumber
SequenceNumberProperty.Description: The task sequence number that is the end of the loopback.

EnumProperty.Name: LoopbackBranchType
EnumProperty.Description:
Indicates whether the loopback is a conditional or probabilistic branch in the task workflow.
If the branch type is 'Conditional', then the loopback occurs if the specified logical condition evaluates to True.
The 'Probabilistic' branch type may be used to identify the loopback as one of possibly several mutually exclusive alternatives at a probabilistic decision point. The sum of the branch probabilities at a probabilistic decision point cannot be greater than one.

ExpressionProperty.Name: LoopbackConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description: The branch condition or probability specified as an expression. If a condition then enter the logical condition. If a probability then enter the chance of the loopback as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).

EnumProperty.Name: ProcessingTaskPrecedenceMethod
EnumProperty.Description: The method used to define the task precedence dependencies. Can be either by specifying task sequence numbers, specifying the immediate predecessors for each task, or specifying the immediate successors for each task.

TableProperty.Name: ProcessingTaskResourcesReferencedTableName
TableProperty.Description: The name of the data table to be used as the referenced data source for getting task resource requirements.

TableProperty.Name: ProcessingTaskMaterialsReferencedTableName
TableProperty.Description: The name of the data table to be used as the referenced data source for getting task material requirements.

TableProperty.Name: ProcessingTaskStateAssignmentsReferencedTableName
TableProperty.DisplayName: Task State Assignments Referenced Table Name
TableProperty.Description: The name of the data table to be used as the referenced data source for getting task state assignments.

ExpressionProperty.Name: ProcessingTaskSequenceRandomNumberStream
ExpressionProperty.DisplayName: Processing Task Sequence Random Number Stream
ExpressionProperty.Description: The random number stream to be used if there is probabilistic branching in the task sequence.

ListProperty.Name: OffShiftRule
ListProperty.Description:
The processing rule used if the server is at the end of a shift because of its specified work schedule.
Suspend Processing - The server will immediately suspend all processing and set its resource state to 'OffShift'. Processing will resume at the start of the next shift.
Finish Work Already Started - The server will not accept any new entities but will continue processing if necessary to finish work already started. The server's resource state will be set to 'OffShiftProcessing' if processing entities during an off-shift period.

EnumProperty.Name: ResourceEfficiencyRule
EnumProperty.Description:
The processing rule used to alter the rate at which work is performed if there are seized resources with defined efficiency values. The actual work duration is the planned work duration divided by the efficiency.
If the rule is None, then seized resource efficiency is ignored.
If the rule is Average, then the average seized resource efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Count, then the number of seized resources with a defined efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Maximum, then the largest efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Minimum, then the smallest efficiency value is used.
If the rule is Sum, then the sum of the seized resource efficiency values is used.

RepeatingProperty.Name: SeizeConstraintLogic
RepeatingProperty.Description:
Constraint logic used to enforce additional constraints on an entity's request to seize the server.
NOTE: This repeat group applies only if the server has an input buffer. Otherwise, if no input buffer, then this constraint logic will be ignored.

ElementProperty.Name: SeizeConstraintLogicName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the Constraint Logic element used to enforce additional constraints on an entity's request to seize the server.

BooleanProperty.Name: ImmediatelyTrySeize
BooleanProperty.Description:
For an arriving entity, indicates whether to immediately try seizing the server before the execution of any other simulation logic in the system and, if successful, skipping the servers allocation queue.
Setting this property to False will just insert the seize request into the servers allocation queue. An evaluation of that queue will then be scheduled on the simulations current event calendar as a late priority event.
NOTE: This property setting applies only if the server has an input buffer. Otherwise, if no input buffer, then an arriving entity will always immediately try to enter the servers processing station and seize it.

BooleanProperty.Name: ImmediatelyTryAllocateWhenReleased
BooleanProperty.Description:
Once an entity has exited processing and released the server, indicates whether to immediately try allocating the released server capacity to waiting seize requests before the execution of any other simulation logic in the system.
Setting this property to False will skip immediate allocation. Instead, an evaluation of the servers allocation queue will be scheduled on the simulations current event calendar as a late priority event.

IntegerProperty.Name: InputBufferCapacity
IntegerProperty.Description: The number of discrete entities that can be held in the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: InputBufferBalkDecisionType
EnumProperty.Description:
The method used by an entity to decide whether to balk at entering the buffer.
If the decision type is Blocked, then an entity attempting to enter the buffer will balk if the buffer is full rather than be blocked. Or, if a zero capacity buffer, the entity will balk if its attempt to transfer directly into or out of the object is blocked.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InputBufferBalkConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description: The balk condition or probability specified as an expression. If a probability then enter the chance of balking as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).

NodeProperty.Name: InputBufferBalkNodeName
NodeProperty.Description: Facility node location to send an entity that has balked at entering the buffer.

RepeatingProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeTriggers
RepeatingProperty.Description: Optional time or event-driven triggers that can cause entities to abandon waiting in the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeTriggerType
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of trigger.
A time based trigger can renege an entity from the buffer once a specified wait duration expires.
An event based trigger can renege an entity from the buffer whenever a specified event occurs.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeWaitDuration
ExpressionProperty.Description: The wait duration until deciding whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

EventProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeTriggeringEventName
EventProperty.Description: The name of the event whose occurrence will trigger a decision whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeDecisionType
EnumProperty.Description: The method used when the trigger has fired to decide whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InputBufferRenegeConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The renege condition or probability specified as an expression. If a probability then enter the chance of reneging as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).

In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource objects (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: SecondaryResourceReleasesBeforeProcessingKeepReservedCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional condition indicating whether to keep the released resource capacity reserved for possible later reuse by the same entity. Other entities will be unable to use a reserved resource unless the reservation is cancelled.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate resource object(s) being released (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).
Note that when an entity is attempting to select a resource from a group of candidates (e.g., from a list or from a population of some resource type), by default a preference will be given to select a resource that has already been reserved by that owner irrespective of the specified selection goal.
Leaving this property blank (no condition) is equivalent to entering False.

ExpressionProperty.Name: SecondaryResourceReleasesBeforeProcessingReservationTimeout
ExpressionProperty.Description:

In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[ObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the resource object(s) being released (e.g., Candidate.Object.Capacity).

ChangeDescriptions.ChangeDescription: Version 2.37: Updated the Source object to provide an 'Initial Number Entities' option for the 'On Event' arrival mode, for creating an initial number of entities at the beginning of the simulation run in addition to entities created by the specified Event Name. Also added a 'Rate Scale Factor' option for the 'Time Varying Arrival Rate' arrival mode, for scaling the arrival rate values specified in the rate table.
Version 2.39: Updated the Source object to provide a 'State Assignments' property category.

Version 2.40: Updated the Source object to provide a 'Table Reference Assignment' property category. In the object process logic, the 'Action' property for all Execute steps executing an 'add-on process' is now specified as 'WaitUntilCompleted'.
Version 2.41: Updated the Source object to provide a 'Stopping Conditions' property category. Updated the assignments repeat groups to take state units into account.
Version 3.42: Changes related to setting the 'Token Associated Object Destroyed Action' option for process logic in this object.

For the 'Arrival Table' arrival mode option, added new 'Arrival Time Deviation','No-Show Probability', and 'Repeat Arrival Pattern' features. Also, to support the 'Maximum Time' stopping condition, the Source object's logic now takes advantage of a new 'Maximum Time' feature in the Timer element rather than using a Delay step-based approach.

DynamicObjectInstanceProperty.Name: EntityType
DynamicObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The type of entities created by this Source object.

EnumProperty.Name: ArrivalMode
EnumProperty.Description: The method used by this Source object to generate a stream of entity arrivals.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TimeOffset
ExpressionProperty.Description: Expression that is evaluated once at the beginning of the simulation run. Indicates the time offset until the first arrival at this Source object.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InterarrivalTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: Expression that is evaluated whenever an arrival occurs at this Source object. Indicates the time until the next arrival. This property may be specified using a random sample from a distribution (typically the exponential distribution).

RateTableProperty.Name: RateTable
RateTableProperty.Description: The rate table that defines how the rate of entity arrival events changes over time, the interarrival times following a non-stationary poisson process.

ExpressionProperty.Name: RateScaleFactor
ExpressionProperty.Description: The factor used to scale the arrival rate values specified in the rate table.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InitialNumberEntities
ExpressionProperty.Description: An initial number of entities to be created by this Source object at the beginning of the simulation run, in addition to entities created by the 'On Event' arrival mode. Note that this initial entity creation is not included in (counted against) the arrival mode's Maximum Arrivals.

EventProperty.Name: TriggeringEventName
EventProperty.Description: The name of the event whose occurrences determine when the next entity arrival occurs at this Source object.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TriggeringEventCount
ExpressionProperty.Description: The number of triggering event occurrences required to trigger the next entity arrival at this Source object.

TableAndColumnProperty.Name: ArrivalTimeProperty
TableAndColumnProperty.Description:
The name of the numeric table property (table column) that contains the discrete times when arrival events are expected to occur.
When an arrival event occurs, a reference to the table row holding the arrival time will be automatically assigned to any individual entities created by the event.

ExpressionProperty.Name: ArrivalEventsPerTimeSlot
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The number of arrival events expected to occur at each of the discrete times defined in the Arrival Time Property. When an arrival event occurs, the actual number of entities created (i.e., the arrival 'batch size') is then determined by the Entities Per Arrival property.
To vary the number of arrival events for each time slot, add a numeric column that contains those values to the referenced arrival table. Then specify the name of that table column here.
ExpressionProperty.Category: Entity Arrival Logic/Other Arrival Stream Options

ExpressionProperty.Name: ArrivalTimeDeviation
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Expression used to model differences (typically random) between the scheduled times in the arrival table and the actual times during a simulation run that each arrival event occurs.
The specified expression may return a negative or positive value. A negative value indicates that the actual arrival time will occur earlier than the scheduled time by that duration. A positive value indicates that the actual arrival time will occur later than the scheduled time by that duration.
To vary the arrival time deviation for each time slot, add an expression column that contains those expressions to the referenced arrival table. Then specify the name of that table column here.
NOTE: This feature is automatically disabled if random sampling in the simulation run is disabled.
ExpressionProperty.Category: Entity Arrival Logic/Other Arrival Stream Options

ExpressionProperty.Name: ArrivalNoShowProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The probability that a scheduled arrival in the arrival pattern will be a no-show and thus the timer's event not actually fired. Enter the chance of a no-show as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).
To vary the no-show probability for each time slot, add a numeric column that contains those probabilities to the referenced arrival table. Then specify the name of that table column here.
NOTE: This feature is automatically disabled if random sampling in the simulation run is disabled.
ExpressionProperty.Category: Entity Arrival Logic/Other Arrival Stream Options

ExpressionProperty.Name: EntitiesPerArrival
ExpressionProperty.Description: The number of entities that will be created by this Source object for each arrival event.

EnumProperty.Name: RepeatingArrivalPattern
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates whether the arrival pattern in the table should be repeated when the end of the pattern is reached.

ExpressionProperty.Name: EntityArrivalsRandomNumberStream
ExpressionProperty.Description: The random number stream used to generate interarrival times (if rate table) or make probabilistic no-show decisions (if arrival table).

ExpressionProperty.Name: MaximumArrivals
ExpressionProperty.Description: A limit on the total number of arrivals to be automatically generated by this Source object during the simulation run.

ExpressionProperty.Name: MaximumTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: The maximum time from the beginning of the simulation run after which this Source object will stop generating arrivals.

EventProperty.Name: StopEventName
EventProperty.Description: The name of an event whose occurrence will trigger this Source object to stop generating arrivals for the remainder of the simulation run.

IntegerProperty.Name: OutputBufferCapacity
IntegerProperty.Description: The number of discrete entities that can be held in the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: OutputBufferBalkDecisionType
EnumProperty.Description:
The method used by an entity to decide whether to balk at entering the buffer.
If the decision type is Blocked, then an entity attempting to enter the buffer will balk if the buffer is full rather than be blocked. Or, if a zero capacity buffer, the entity will balk if its attempt to transfer directly into or out of the object is blocked.

ExpressionProperty.Name: OutputBufferBalkConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description: The balk condition or probability specified as an expression. If a probability then enter the chance of balking as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).

NodeProperty.Name: OutputBufferBalkNodeName
NodeProperty.Description: Facility node location to send an entity that has balked at entering the buffer.

RepeatingProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeTriggers
RepeatingProperty.Description: Optional time or event-driven triggers that can cause entities to abandon waiting in the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeTriggerType
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of trigger.
A time based trigger can renege an entity from the buffer once a specified wait duration expires.
An event based trigger can renege an entity from the buffer whenever a specified event occurs.

ExpressionProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeWaitDuration
ExpressionProperty.Description: The wait duration until deciding whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

EventProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeTriggeringEventName
EventProperty.Description: The name of the event whose occurrence will trigger a decision whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

EnumProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeDecisionType
EnumProperty.Description: The method used when the trigger has fired to decide whether to renege an entity from the buffer.

ExpressionProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeConditionOrProbability
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The renege condition or probability specified as an expression. If a probability then enter the chance of reneging as a value between 0.0 (0%) and 1.0 (100%).
NOTE: If it is necessary to check in a conditional expression whether an entity is currently waiting for a specific type of constraint, the entity Queuing namespace provides several functions for that purpose (e.g., Entity.Queuing.IsWaitingRidePickupQueue).

NodeProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeNodeName
NodeProperty.Description: Facility node location to send a reneging entity.

EnumProperty.Name: OutputBufferRenegeTriggerStartBoundary
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates when the trigger becomes active for an entity occupying the buffer. Can be either immediately when the entity has entered the buffer or, alternatively, not until its transfer into the buffer has been ended (e.g., after a transfer-in time or any other entry related logic).

EnumProperty.Name: TableRowReferenceBeforeCreatingEntitiesActionType
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of table row reference action to perform.
The Reference Existing Row action type may be used to set a reference to an existing row in a data table or sequence table. The row index into the table is specified by the Row Number property.
The Add New Row action type may be used to add a new row to an output table. A reference will be automatically set to the newly added row.

The Add New Row action type may be used to add a new row to an output table. A reference will be automatically set to the newly added row.

NodeDefinition.Name: TransferNode
NodeDefinition.Author: Simio Employee
NodeDefinition.Description: A TransferNode object may be used by an entity to transfer into or out of an object. This type of node may also be used to define an intersection point in a network of links. Optional entity destination selection and transport logic is provided.

ChangeDescriptions.ChangeDescription: Version 2.36: Renamed the 'TransferToLinkFailureLogic' process in the TransferNode process logic to 'TransferFailureLogic'. If the 'AutoTransferOnEntry' property value of the TransferNode is 'To Parent External Node' and the transfer to the specified parent external node fails, then the token now executes the 'TransferFailureLogic' process.
Version 2.37: Changed 'Capacity' display name to 'Initial Capacity' as object capacities are now user assignable.
Version 2.38: The RoutingGroup element named 'RoutingOut' that is owned by the TransferNode is now a private element.

Version 2.39: Updated the TransferNode object process logic to specify all of the object's process delays as non-interruptible. For the 'Select From List' feature to set an entity's next destination, changed the default value of the destination 'Selection Expression' property to be 'Candidate.Node.InputLocation.Overload'.
Version 2.40: In the object process logic, the 'Action' property for all Execute steps executing an 'add-on process' is now specified as 'WaitUntilCompleted'.
Version 2.41: Minor property description and display name updates. The RoutingGroup element named 'RoutingOut' that is owned by the TransferNode is now a public element.

ListProperty.Name: DestinationType
ListProperty.Description:
The method used to set a destination node for entities exiting the transfer node.
If the method is 'By Sequence', then the entity must have a sequence table assigned. The destination node value will be set to the next destination in the sequence.
Either the Select From List or Use Custom Routing Group methods may be used to route an entity to a location selected from a list of possible destination nodes. Note that the custom routing group approach can be particularly useful if it is desirable to have a single logical queue for entities waiting to be routed that is shared between multiple transfer node locations. Refer to the Routing Group element for more information.

NodeProperty.Name: DestinationNodeName
NodeProperty.Description: The name of the specific node that is the destination.

NodeListProperty.Name: DestinationNodeListName
NodeListProperty.Description: Identifies the list of possible destination nodes.

ElementProperty.Name: DestinationRoutingGroupName
ElementProperty.Description:
The name of the Routing Group element that will be used to route each entity to a location selected from a list of possible destination nodes.
Go to Definitions->Elements to add a new Routing Group element to the model.

EnumProperty.Name: DestinationSelectionGoal
EnumProperty.Description: The goal used to select a destination if there are multiple candidates available in the list of possible destination nodes.

ExpressionProperty.Name: DestinationSelectionExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The expression used to get the value for each candidate destination node.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[NodeClass].[Attribute] or Candidate.[NodeAssociatedObjectClass].[Attribute] to evaluate attributes of either the candidate destination nodes themselves or the objects associated with those candidate nodes (e.g., Candidate.Node.AssociatedStation.Capacity or Candidate.Server.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: DestinationSelectionCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional condition evaluated for each candidate destination node that must be true for the node to be selected.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[NodeClass].[Attribute] or Candidate.[NodeAssociatedObjectClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of either the candidate destination nodes themselves or the objects associated with those candidate nodes (e.g., Candidate.Node.AssociatedStation.Capacity or Candidate.Server.Capacity).

EnumProperty.Name: BlockedDestinationRule
EnumProperty.Description:
The rule used to manage destination selection if there are one or more candidates in the list of possible destination nodes that have no space available.
If the rule is 'Select Any', then whether or not a destination is blocked will be ignored.
If the rule is 'Select Available Only', then only a destination that is not currently blocked may be assigned, and if all possible destinations are blocked then an entity will be held at the TransferNode until a destination becomes available.
If the rule is 'Prefer Available', then a destination that is not currently blocked will be preferred, but if all possible destinations are blocked then the best destination per the selection goal will still be immediately assigned.

RepeatingProperty.Name: RouteConstraintLogic
RepeatingProperty.Description: Constraint logic used to enforce additional constraints on an entitys route request.

ElementProperty.Name: RouteConstraintLogicName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the Constraint Logic element used to enforce additional constraints on an entitys route request.

EnumProperty.Name: RouteRequestRankingRule
EnumProperty.Description: The static rule used to rank competing entities waiting to be assigned an available destination.

ExpressionProperty.Name: RouteRequestRankingExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description: The expression used with a Smallest Value First or Largest Value First ranking rule.

SelectionRuleProperty.Name: RouteRequestDynamicSelectionRule
SelectionRuleProperty.Description: The rule used to dynamically select an entity from competing requests waiting to be assigned an available destination.

ListProperty.Name: RideOnTransporter
ListProperty.Description: Indicates whether an entity must ride a transporter to exit the transfer node.

ExpressionProperty.Name: RideOnTransporterCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: The condition expression indicating whether an entity must ride a transporter to exit the transfer node.

EnumProperty.Name: TransporterType
EnumProperty.Description: The method for specifying the transporter object to ride.

ObjectInstanceProperty.Name: TransporterName
ObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The name of the transporter object to ride.

TransporterListProperty.Name: TransporterListName
TransporterListProperty.Description: The name of the transporter list from which to select the transporter object to ride.

EnumProperty.Name: TransporterReservationMethod
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of reservation method used to select a transporter object to ride.
Reserve Closest - Reserve the transporter that is closest to the transfer node. The rule used to break ties is the specified selection goal.
Reserve Best - Reserve the transporter using the specified selection goal. The rule used to break ties is the transporter that is closest to the transfer node.
First Available At Location - Can only select a transporter that is already located at the transfer node. The rule used to break ties is the specified selection goal.

EnumProperty.Name: TransporterSelectionGoal
EnumProperty.Description: The rule used in conjunction with the specified reservation method to select a transporter object from multiple candidates.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TransporterSelectionValueExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description:
The expression used to get the value for each candidate transporter.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[TransporterClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate transporter objects (e.g., Candidate.Transporter.RideStation.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: TransporterSelectionCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional condition evaluated for each candidate transporter that must be true for the transporter to be selected.
In the expression, use the syntax Candidate.[TransporterClass].[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the candidate transporter objects (e.g., Candidate.Transporter.RideStation.Capacity).

ExpressionProperty.Name: TransporterStatusOnDropOffKeepReservedCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description:
Optional condition indicating whether, on drop-off, to keep the transporter resource reserved for possible later reuse by the same entity. Other entities will be unable to use the reserved transporter for processing tasks or new ride pickup requests unless the reservation is cancelled.
This condition is evaluated when the entity is picked up at the TransferNode. In the expression, use the syntax Entity.CurrentTransporter.[Attribute] to reference an attribute of the selected transporter (e.g., Entity.CurrentTransporter.Is.Vehicle1).
Note that when an entity is attempting to select a resource from a group of candidates (e.g., from a list or from a population of some resource type), by default a preference will be given to select a resource that has already been reserved by that entity irrespective of the specified selection goal.
Leaving this property blank (no condition) is equivalent to entering False.

ExpressionProperty.Name: AssignmentsOnEnteringAssignCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: The condition required to perform the assignment.

ExpressionProperty.Name: AssignmentsOnEnteringNewValue

ListProperty.Description: Condition required to record the tally statistic.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TalliesOnEnteringTallyCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: The condition required to record the tally statistic.

ElementProperty.Name: TalliesOnEnteringTallyStatisticName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the tally statistic for which to record an observation value.

EnumProperty.Name: TalliesOnEnteringValueType
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of observation value to record.
If the value type is 'Expression', then the value of the specified expression is recorded.
If the value type is 'TimeBetween', then the time since the last entity arrival to this or any other Tally step referencing the tally statistic is recorded.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TalliesOnEnteringValueExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description: The expression returning the value to be recorded.

RepeatingProperty.Name: TalliesOnExited
RepeatingProperty.Description: Optional tally statistics to record when an entity has exited the node.

ListProperty.Name: TalliesOnExitedTallyConditionType
ListProperty.Description: Condition required to record the tally statistic.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TalliesOnExitedTallyCondition
ExpressionProperty.Description: The condition required to record the tally statistic.

ElementProperty.Name: TalliesOnExitedTallyStatisticName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the tally statistic for which to record an observation value.

EnumProperty.Name: TalliesOnExitedValueType
EnumProperty.Description:
The type of observation value to record.
If the value type is 'Expression', then the value of the specified expression is recorded.
If the value type is 'TimeBetween', then the time since the last entity arrival to this or any other Tally step referencing the tally statistic is recorded.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TalliesOnExitedValueExpression
ExpressionProperty.Description: The expression returning the value to be recorded.

ElementProperty.Name: RunEndingAddOnProcess
ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when the simulation run is ending.

ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when an entity's leading edge has entered this node.

ElementProperty.Name: ExitedAddOnProcess
ElementProperty.Description: Occurs when an entity's trailing edge has exited this node.

ExternalNodeProperty.Name: BoundExternalOutputNode
ExternalNodeProperty.Description: The name of an external output node that this node has been bound to in order to transfer entities out of the containing (parent) object. The transfer attempt will be performed by an entity after entering the node and, if successful, any other crossing or routing logic for the node will be ignored.

RepeatingProperty.Name: RoutingOutRequiredMaterials
RepeatingProperty.Description:
Additional material availability constraints enforced on an entity's route request.
NOTE: This repeat group has been deprecated. Use the Routing Logic -> Other Routing Options -> Route Constraint Logic property instead. To edit the deprecated repeat group, go to File -> Settings -> GUI and set the Display Deprecated Properties in Properties Window value to True.

EnumProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialConsumptionType
EnumProperty.Description: Indicates whether the material required to be available for consumption is a single material or a bill of materials.

ElementProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialName
ElementProperty.Description: The name of the material which is either specifically required or whose bill of materials is required.

EnumProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialInventorySiteType
EnumProperty.Description:
Indicates the fixed object that is the inventory location. Applies only to material elements whose Location Based Inventory property is set to True.
The 'ParentObject' setting may be used to indicate that the inventory site is the server, combiner, or separator.

ObjectInstanceProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialSiteObjectName
ObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The name of the fixed object that is the inventory location.

ExpressionProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialQuantity
ExpressionProperty.Description: The quantity required.

ExpressionProperty.Name: RequiredMaterialLotID
ExpressionProperty.Description: Optional string value indicating the lot identifier of the required material.

Override.Name: InitialTravelerCapacity
Override.Description:
The initial maximum number of traveling entities that may simultaneously occupy this node.
NOTE: An entity using the 'Ride On Transporter' option at this transfer node will be exempted from being blocked by or counted against the node's traveler capacity limit. Also, refer to the user-assignable CurrentTravelerCapacity state variable of a node to dynamically change its traveler capacity during a simulation run.

Event.Description: The Entered event provides notification that an entity has entered the node.

Event.Name: Exited
Event.Description: The Exited event provides notification that an entity has exited the node.

Event.Name: RiderWaiting
Event.Description: The RiderWaiting event provides notification that an entity has entered the RidePickupQueue of the node waiting for a ride.
